---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="better-worktree docs"
  description="A git worktree manager with one-off commands and a keyboard-first TUI."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Git worktree workflow</p>
    <h1>Ship branches faster with less path juggling.</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      <code>bwt</code> keeps your repos and worktrees in one place, so creating, switching,
      and cleaning up branches is one command or keypress away.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>One-off commands</h3>
      <p class="muted">
        List, create, and delete worktrees from scripts or your terminal without entering the
        interactive UI.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Keyboard-first TUI</h3>
      <p class="muted">
        Open without arguments to browse repos, inspect statuses, and manage worktrees quickly.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Repo-aware defaults</h3>
      <p class="muted">
        Save repository paths and copy rules in config so new worktrees start with the files you
        need.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
